<heading id="D08281EBFFDFFFD3FF12FE4315E7C2BA" box="[218,684,460,482]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="8" pageNumber="705" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFDFFFD3FF12FE4315E7C2BA" authority="(CURRAN, 1939)" baseAuthorityName="Curran" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[218,684,460,482]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="705" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachecoi">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFDFFFD3FF12FE4316A1C2B8" box="[218,490,461,482]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="705">COPESTYLUM PACHECOI</emphasis>
(CURRAN, 1939)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFDFFFD3FF58FE7D16D9C044" blockId="8.[144,759,499,796]" pageId="8" pageNumber="705">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFDFFFD3FF58FE7D1641C150" box="[144,266,499,520]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="705">Puparium:</emphasis>
Anterior fold without extra large spicules. Anterior spiracles with three openings. Anterodorsal margin of metathorax with some spicules. Abdominal vestiture of long, fine setae. Anal lobe with spicules. Posterior breathing tube orange, not tapering. AP smooth and shiny and about 1.2¥ as long as TR is wide. Pupal spiracles orange, matt, shining apically, and with three encircling rings of openings in upper half. Pupal spiracles about 1.5¥ as wide apart as a pupal spiracle is long.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36F650CFFDFFFD3FF58FCC61595C70F" pageId="8" pageNumber="705" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFDFFFD3FF58FCC6168EC080" blockId="8.[144,759,840,984]" pageId="8" pageNumber="705">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFDFFFD3FF58FCC6151DC005" box="[144,598,840,861]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="705">
Taxonomic notes: 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFDFFFD3FEACFCC6151DC005" baseAuthorityName="Curran" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[356,598,840,861]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="705" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pachecoi">Copestylum pachecoi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is similar to those Pictum group species with a nontapering posterior breathing tube. It differs from these species in having spicules and broad setae on the anterodorsal margin of the metathorax.
</paragraph>
